label: Thing
comment: The most generic type of item.

properties.label: additionalType
properties.comment: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.

properties.label: alternateName
properties.comment: An alias for the item.

properties.label: description
properties.comment: A short description of the item.

properties.label: image
properties.comment: URL of an image of the item.

properties.label: name
properties.comment: The name of the item.

properties.label: sameAs
properties.comment: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Freebase page, or official website.

properties.label: url
properties.comment: URL of the item.

properties.label: potentialAction
properties.comment: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.

label: CreativeWork
comment: The most generic kind of creative work, including books, movies, photographs, software programs, etc.

properties.label: about
properties.comment: The subject matter of the content.

properties.label: accessibilityAPI
properties.comment: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

properties.label: accessibilityControl
properties.comment: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

properties.label: accessibilityFeature
properties.comment: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

properties.label: accessibilityHazard
properties.comment: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3. (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values)

properties.label: accountablePerson
properties.comment: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

properties.label: aggregateRating
properties.comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

properties.label: alternativeHeadline
properties.comment: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

properties.label: associatedMedia
properties.comment: The media objects that encode this creative work. This property is a synonym for encodings.

properties.label: audience
properties.comment: The intended audience of the item, i.e. the group for whom the item was created.

properties.label: audio
properties.comment: An embedded audio object.

properties.label: author
properties.comment: The author of this content. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

properties.label: award
properties.comment: An award won by this person or for this creative work.

properties.label: citation
properties.comment: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

properties.label: comment
properties.comment: Comments, typically from users, on this CreativeWork.

properties.label: contentLocation
properties.comment: The location of the content.

properties.label: contentRating
properties.comment: Official rating of a piece of content—for example,'MPAA PG-13'.

properties.label: contributor
properties.comment: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork.

properties.label: copyrightHolder
properties.comment: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

properties.label: copyrightYear
properties.comment: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

properties.label: creator
properties.comment: The creator/author of this CreativeWork or UserComments. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

properties.label: dateCreated
properties.comment: The date on which the CreativeWork was created.

properties.label: dateModified
properties.comment: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified.

properties.label: datePublished
properties.comment: Date of first broadcast/publication.

properties.label: discussionUrl
properties.comment: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

properties.label: editor
properties.comment: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

properties.label: educationalAlignment
properties.comment: An alignment to an established educational framework.

properties.label: educationalUse
properties.comment: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

properties.label: encoding
properties.comment: A media object that encode this CreativeWork.

properties.label: genre
properties.comment: Genre of the creative work

properties.label: headline
properties.comment: Headline of the article

properties.label: inLanguage
properties.comment: The language of the content. please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard.

properties.label: interactionCount
properties.comment: A count of a specific user interactions with this item—for example, 20 UserLikes, 5 UserComments, or 300 UserDownloads. The user interaction type should be one of the sub types of UserInteraction.

properties.label: interactivityType
properties.comment: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

properties.label: isBasedOnUrl
properties.comment: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html

properties.label: isFamilyFriendly
properties.comment: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

properties.label: keywords
properties.comment: Keywords or tags used to describe this content. Multiple entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas.

properties.label: license
properties.comment: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

properties.label: learningResourceType
properties.comment: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

properties.label: mentions
properties.comment: Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

properties.label: offers
properties.comment: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, or give away tickets to an event.

properties.label: publisher
properties.comment: The publisher of the creative work.

properties.label: publishingPrinciples
properties.comment: Link to page describing the editorial principles of the organization primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.

properties.label: review
properties.comment: A review of the item.

properties.label: sourceOrganization
properties.comment: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

properties.label: text
properties.comment: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

properties.label: thumbnailUrl
properties.comment: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

properties.label: timeRequired
properties.comment: Approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience, e.g. 'P30M', 'P1H25M'.

properties.label: typicalAgeRange
properties.comment: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

properties.label: version
properties.comment: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

properties.label: video
properties.comment: An embedded video object.

properties.label: provider
properties.comment: The person or organization providing the service, reservation, or creative work. The provider may subcontract out the service.

properties.label: commentCount
properties.comment: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

label: WebPage
comment: A web page. Every web page is implicitly assumed to be declared to be of type WebPage, so the various properties about that webpage, such as breadcrumb may be used. We recommend explicit declaration if these properties are specified, but if they are found outside of an itemscope, they will be assumed to be about the page

properties.label: breadcrumb
properties.comment: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

properties.label: isPartOf
properties.comment: Indicates the collection or gallery to which the item belongs.

properties.label: lastReviewed
properties.comment: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.

properties.label: mainContentOfPage
properties.comment: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

properties.label: primaryImageOfPage
properties.comment: Indicates the main image on the page.

properties.label: relatedLink
properties.comment: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.

properties.label: reviewedBy
properties.comment: People or organizations that have reviewed the content on this web page for accuracy and/or completeness.

properties.label: significantLink
properties.comment: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

properties.label: specialty
properties.comment: One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.

label: AboutPage
comment: Web page type: About page.

label: Organization
comment: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.

properties.label: address
properties.comment: Physical address of the item.

properties.label: aggregateRating
properties.comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

properties.label: brand
properties.comment: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

properties.label: contactPoint
properties.comment: A contact point for a person or organization.

properties.label: department
properties.comment: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

properties.label: duns
properties.comment: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

properties.label: email
properties.comment: Email address.

properties.label: employee
properties.comment: Someone working for this organization.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place or organization.

properties.label: faxNumber
properties.comment: The fax number.

properties.label: founder
properties.comment: A person who founded this organization.

properties.label: dissolutionDate
properties.comment: The date that this organization was dissolved.

properties.label: foundingDate
properties.comment: The date that this organization was founded.

properties.label: globalLocationNumber
properties.comment: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

properties.label: hasPOS
properties.comment: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

properties.label: interactionCount
properties.comment: A count of a specific user interactions with this item—for example, 20 UserLikes, 5 UserComments, or 300 UserDownloads. The user interaction type should be one of the sub types of UserInteraction.

properties.label: isicV4
properties.comment: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

properties.label: legalName
properties.comment: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

properties.label: location
properties.comment: The location of the event, organization or action.

properties.label: logo
properties.comment: A logo associated with an organization.

properties.label: makesOffer
properties.comment: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

properties.label: member
properties.comment: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

properties.label: memberOf
properties.comment: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

properties.label: naics
properties.comment: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

properties.label: owns
properties.comment: Products owned by the organization or person.

properties.label: review
properties.comment: A review of the item.

properties.label: seeks
properties.comment: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

properties.label: subOrganization
properties.comment: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

properties.label: taxID
properties.comment: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

properties.label: telephone
properties.comment: The telephone number.

properties.label: vatID
properties.comment: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

label: Place
comment: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

properties.label: address
properties.comment: Physical address of the item.

properties.label: aggregateRating
properties.comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

properties.label: containedIn
properties.comment: The basic containment relation between places.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place or organization.

properties.label: faxNumber
properties.comment: The fax number.

properties.label: geo
properties.comment: The geo coordinates of the place.

properties.label: globalLocationNumber
properties.comment: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

properties.label: interactionCount
properties.comment: A count of a specific user interactions with this item—for example, 20 UserLikes, 5 UserComments, or 300 UserDownloads. The user interaction type should be one of the sub types of UserInteraction.

properties.label: isicV4
properties.comment: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

properties.label: logo
properties.comment: A logo associated with an organization.

properties.label: hasMap
properties.comment: A URL to a map of the place.

properties.label: openingHoursSpecification
properties.comment: The opening hours of a certain place.

properties.label: photo
properties.comment: A photograph of this place.

properties.label: review
properties.comment: A review of the item.

properties.label: telephone
properties.comment: The telephone number.

label: LocalBusiness
comment: A particular physical business or branch of an organization. Examples of LocalBusiness include a restaurant, a particular branch of a restaurant chain, a branch of a bank, a medical practice, a club, a bowling alley, etc.

properties.label: branchOf
properties.comment: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any.

properties.label: currenciesAccepted
properties.comment: The currency accepted (in ISO 4217 currency format).

properties.label: openingHours
properties.comment:
The opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.
- Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
- Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
- Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
- If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

properties.label: paymentAccepted
properties.comment: Cash, credit card, etc.

properties.label: priceRange
properties.comment: The price range of the business, for example $$$.

label: FinancialService
comment: Financial services business.

label: ProfessionalService
comment: Provider of professional services.

label: AccountingService
comment: Accountancy business.

label: AdministrativeArea
comment: A geographical region under the jurisdiction of a particular government.

label: EntertainmentBusiness
comment: A business providing entertainment.

label: AdultEntertainment
comment: An adult entertainment establishment.

label: Intangible
comment: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things such as quantities, structured values, etc.

label: Offer
comment: An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service—for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.

properties.label: acceptedPaymentMethod
properties.comment: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.

properties.label: addOn
properties.comment: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

properties.label: advanceBookingRequirement
properties.comment: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

properties.label: aggregateRating
properties.comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

properties.label: availability
properties.comment: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

properties.label: availabilityEnds
properties.comment: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

properties.label: availabilityStarts
properties.comment: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

properties.label: availableAtOrFrom
properties.comment: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

properties.label: availableDeliveryMethod
properties.comment: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

properties.label: businessFunction
properties.comment: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

properties.label: category
properties.comment: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

properties.label: deliveryLeadTime
properties.comment: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods leaving the warehouse.

properties.label: eligibleCustomerType
properties.comment: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

properties.label: eligibleDuration
properties.comment: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

properties.label: eligibleQuantity
properties.comment: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

properties.label: eligibleRegion
properties.comment: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.

properties.label: eligibleTransactionVolume
properties.comment: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

properties.label: gtin13
properties.comment: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceeding zero.

properties.label: gtin14
properties.comment: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

properties.label: gtin8
properties.comment: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN.

properties.label: includesObject
properties.comment: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in the offer.

properties.label: inventoryLevel
properties.comment: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

properties.label: itemCondition
properties.comment: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition or a textual description of the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer.

properties.label: itemOffered
properties.comment: The item being offered.

properties.label: mpn
properties.comment: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

properties.label: price
properties.comment: The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

properties.label: priceSpecification
properties.comment: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

properties.label: priceValidUntil
properties.comment: The date after which the price is no longer available.

properties.label: review
properties.comment: A review of the item.

properties.label: seller
properties.comment: The organization or person making the offer.

properties.label: serialNumber
properties.comment: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

properties.label: sku
properties.comment: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

properties.label: validFrom
properties.comment: The date when the item becomes valid.

properties.label: validThrough
properties.comment: The end of the validity of offer, price specification, or opening hours data.

properties.label: warranty
properties.comment: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

properties.label: priceCurrency
properties.comment: The currency (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format) of the price or a price component, when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

label: AggregateOffer
comment: When a single product is associated with multiple offers (for example, the same pair of shoes is offered by different merchants), then AggregateOffer can be used.

properties.label: highPrice
properties.comment: The highest price of all offers available.

properties.label: lowPrice
properties.comment: The lowest price of all offers available.

properties.label: offerCount
properties.comment: The number of offers for the product.

label: Rating
comment: The rating of the video.

properties.label: bestRating
properties.comment: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.

properties.label: ratingValue
properties.comment: The rating for the content.

properties.label: worstRating
properties.comment: The lowest value allowed in this rating system. If worstRating is omitted, 1 is assumed.

label: AggregateRating
comment: The average rating based on multiple ratings or reviews.

properties.label: itemReviewed
properties.comment: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

properties.label: ratingCount
properties.comment: The count of total number of ratings.

properties.label: reviewCount
properties.comment: The count of total number of reviews.

label: CivicStructure
comment: A public structure, such as a town hall or concert hall.

properties.label: openingHours
properties.comment:
The opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.
- Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
- Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
- Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
- If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

label: Airport
comment: An airport.

properties.label: iataCode
properties.comment: IATA identifier for an airline or airport

properties.label: iacoCode
properties.comment: IACO identifier for an airport.

label: AmusementPark
comment: An amusement park.

label: MedicalEntity
comment: The most generic type of entity related to health and the practice of medicine.

properties.label: alternateName
properties.comment: An alias for the item.

properties.label: code
properties.comment: A medical code for the entity, taken from a controlled vocabulary or ontology such as ICD-9, DiseasesDB, MeSH, SNOMED-CT, RxNorm, etc.

properties.label: guideline
properties.comment: A medical guideline related to this entity.

properties.label: medicineSystem
properties.comment: The system of medicine that includes this MedicalEntity, for example 'evidence-based', 'homeopathic', 'chiropractic', etc.

properties.label: recognizingAuthority
properties.comment: If applicable, the organization that officially recognizes this entity as part of its endorsed system of medicine.

properties.label: relevantSpecialty
properties.comment: If applicable, a medical specialty in which this entity is relevant.

properties.label: study
properties.comment: A medical study or trial related to this entity.

label: AnatomicalStructure
comment: Any part of the human body, typically a component of an anatomical system. Organs, tissues, and cells are all anatomical structures.

properties.label: associatedPathophysiology
properties.comment: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

properties.label: bodyLocation
properties.comment: Location in the body of the anatomical structure.

properties.label: connectedTo
properties.comment: Other anatomical structures to which this structure is connected.

properties.label: diagram
properties.comment: An image containing a diagram that illustrates the structure and/or its component substructures and/or connections with other structures.

properties.label: function
properties.comment: Function of the anatomical structure.

properties.label: partOfSystem
properties.comment: The anatomical or organ system that this structure is part of.

properties.label: relatedCondition
properties.comment: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

properties.label: relatedTherapy
properties.comment: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

properties.label: subStructure
properties.comment: Component (sub-)structure(s) that comprise this anatomical structure.

label: AnatomicalSystem
comment: An anatomical system is a group of anatomical structures that work together to perform a certain task. Anatomical systems, such as organ systems, are one organizing principle of anatomy, and can includes circulatory, digestive, endocrine, integumentary, immune, lymphatic, muscular, nervous, reproductive, respiratory, skeletal, urinary, vestibular, and other systems.

properties.label: associatedPathophysiology
properties.comment: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

properties.label: comprisedOf
properties.comment: The underlying anatomical structures, such as organs, that comprise the anatomical system.

properties.label: relatedCondition
properties.comment: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

properties.label: relatedStructure
properties.comment: Related anatomical structure(s) that are not part of the system but relate or connect to it, such as vascular bundles associated with an organ system.

properties.label: relatedTherapy
properties.comment: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

label: AnimalShelter
comment: Animal shelter.

label: Residence
comment: The place where a person lives.

label: ApartmentComplex
comment: Residence type: Apartment complex.

label: MedicalIndication
comment: A condition or factor that indicates use of a medical therapy, including signs, symptoms, risk factors, anatomical states, etc.

label: ApprovedIndication
comment: An indication for a medical therapy that has been formally specified or approved by a regulatory body that regulates use of the therapy; for example, the US FDA approves indications for most drugs in the US.

label: Aquarium
comment: Aquarium.

label: ArtGallery
comment: An art gallery.

label: Vessel
comment: A component of the human body circulatory system comprised of an intricate network of hollow tubes that transport blood throughout the entire body.

label: Artery
comment: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries blood away from the heart.

properties.label: arterialBranch
properties.comment: The branches that comprise the arterial structure.

properties.label: source
properties.comment: The anatomical or organ system that the artery originates from.

properties.label: supplyTo
properties.comment: The area to which the artery supplies blood.

label: Article
comment: An article, such as a news article or piece of investigative report. Newspapers and magazines have articles of many different types and this is intended to cover them all.

properties.label: articleBody
properties.comment: The actual body of the article.

properties.label: articleSection
properties.comment: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.

properties.label: wordCount
properties.comment: The number of words in the text of the Article.

label: Attorney
comment: Professional service: Attorney.

label: Audience
comment: Intended audience for an item, i.e. the group for whom the item was created.

properties.label: audienceType
properties.comment:
The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.)
          domain: Audience

properties.label: geographicArea
properties.comment: The geographic area associated with the audience.

label: MediaObject
comment: An image, video, or audio object embedded in a web page. Note that a creative work may have many media objects associated with it on the same web page. For example, a page about a single song (MusicRecording) may have a music video (VideoObject), and a high and low bandwidth audio stream (2 AudioObject's).

properties.label: associatedArticle
properties.comment: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

properties.label: bitrate
properties.comment: The bitrate of the media object.

properties.label: contentSize
properties.comment: File size in (mega/kilo) bytes.

properties.label: contentUrl
properties.comment: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file. (previous spelling: contentURL)

properties.label: duration
properties.comment: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in ISO 8601 date format.

properties.label: embedUrl
properties.comment: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the src element of an embed tag and should not be the same as the content of the loc tag. (previous spelling: embedURL)

properties.label: encodesCreativeWork
properties.comment: The creative work encoded by this media object

properties.label: encodingFormat
properties.comment: mp3, mpeg4, etc.

properties.label: expires
properties.comment: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. Useful for videos.

properties.label: height
properties.comment: The height of the item.

properties.label: interactionCount
properties.comment: A count of a specific user interactions with this item—for example, 20 UserLikes, 5 UserComments, or 300 UserDownloads. The user interaction type should be one of the sub types of UserInteraction.

properties.label: offers
properties.comment: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, or give away tickets to an event.

properties.label: playerType
properties.comment: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

properties.label: productionCompany
properties.comment: The production company or studio that made the movie, tv/radio series, season, or episode, or media object.

properties.label: adverseOutcome
properties.comment: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. properties.label: contraindication

properties.label: duplicateTherapy

properties.label: seriousAdverseOutcome
properties.comment: A possible serious complication and/or serious side effect of this therapy. label: MedicalCondition

properties.label: associatedAnatomy
properties.comment: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

properties.label: cause
properties.comment: An underlying cause. More specifically, one of the causative agent(s) that are most directly responsible for the pathophysiologic process that eventually results in the occurrence.

properties.label: differentialDiagnosis
properties.comment: One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.

properties.label: epidemiology
properties.comment: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

properties.label: expectedPrognosis
properties.comment: The likely outcome in either the short term or long term of the medical condition.

properties.label: naturalProgression
properties.comment: The expected progression of the condition if it is not treated and allowed to progress naturally.

properties.label: pathophysiology
properties.comment: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

properties.label: possibleComplication
properties.comment: A possible unexpected and unfavorable evolution of a medical condition. Complications may include worsening of the signs or symptoms of the disease, extension of the condition to other organ systems, etc.

properties.label: possibleTreatment
properties.comment: A possible treatment to address this condition, sign or symptom.

properties.label: primaryPrevention
properties.comment: A preventative therapy used to prevent an initial occurrence of the medical condition, such as vaccination.

properties.label: riskFactor
properties.comment: A modifiable or non-modifiable factor that increases the risk of a patient contracting this condition, e.g. age,  coexisting condition.

properties.label: secondaryPrevention
properties.comment: A preventative therapy used to prevent reoccurrence of the medical condition after an initial episode of the condition.

properties.label: signOrSymptom
properties.comment: A sign or symptom of this condition. Signs are objective or physically observable manifestations of the medical condition while symptoms are the subjective experience of the medical condition.

properties.label: stage
properties.comment: The stage of the condition, if applicable.

properties.label: subtype
properties.comment: A more specific type of the condition, where applicable, for example 'Type 1 Diabetes', 'Type 2 Diabetes', or 'Gestational Diabetes' for Diabetes.

properties.label: typicalTest
properties.comment: A medical test typically performed given this condition.

label: InfectiousDisease
comment: An infectious disease is a clinically evident human disease resulting from the presence of pathogenic microbial agents, like pathogenic viruses, pathogenic bacteria, fungi, protozoa, multicellular parasites, and prions. To be considered an infectious disease, such pathogens are known to be able to cause this disease.

properties.label: infectiousAgent
properties.comment: The actual infectious agent, such as a specific bacterium.

properties.label: infectiousAgentClass

properties.label: transmissionMethod

properties.label: responsibilities

properties.label: salaryCurrency
properties.comment: The currency (coded using ISO 4217, http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217 used for the main salary information in this job posting.

properties.label: skills

properties.comment: Any special commitments associated with this job posting. Valid entries include VeteranCommit, MilitarySpouseCommit, etc.

label: MedicalCause
comment:
The causative agent(s) that are responsible for the pathophysiologic process that eventually results in a medical condition, symptom or sign. In this schema, unless otherwise specified this is meant to be the proximate cause of the medical condition, symptom or sign. The proximate cause is defined as the causative agent that most directly results in the medical condition, symptom or sign. For example, the HIV virus could be considered a cause of AIDS. Or in a diagnostic context, if a patient fell and sustained a hip fracture and two days later sustained a pulmonary embolism which eventuated in a cardiac arrest, the cause of the cardiac arrest (the proximate cause) would be the pulmonary embolism and not the fall.

Medical causes can include cardiovascular, chemical, dermatologic, endocrine, environmental, gastroenterologic, genetic, hematologic, gynecologic, iatrogenic, infectious, musculoskeletal, neurologic, nutritional, obstetric, oncologic, otolaryngologic, pharmacologic, psychiatric, pulmonary, renal, rheumatologic, toxic, traumatic, or urologic causes; medical conditions can be causes as well.

properties.label: causeOf
properties.comment: The condition, complication, symptom, sign, etc. caused.

label: MedicalClinic
comment: A medical clinic.

properties.label: availableService
properties.comment: A medical service available from this provider.

properties.label: medicalSpecialty
properties.comment: A medical specialty of the provider.

label: MedicalCode
comment: A code for a medical entity.

properties.label: codeValue
properties.comment: The actual code.

properties.label: codingSystem
properties.comment: The coding system, e.g. 'ICD-10'.

label: MedicalConditionStage
comment: A stage of a medical condition, such as 'Stage IIIa'.

properties.label: stageAsNumber
properties.comment: The stage represented as a number, e.g. 3.

properties.label: subStageSuffix
properties.comment: The substage, e.g. 'a' for Stage IIIa.

label: MedicalContraindication
comment: A condition or factor that serves as a reason to withhold a certain medical therapy. Contraindications can be absolute (there are no reasonable circumstances for undertaking a course of action) or relative (the patient is at higher risk of complications, but that these risks may be outweighed by other considerations or mitigated by other measures).

label: MedicalDevice
comment: Any object used in a medical capacity, such as to diagnose or treat a patient.

properties.label: adverseOutcome
properties.comment: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or is otherwise life-threatening or requires immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriouseAdverseOutcome instead.

properties.label: contraindication
properties.comment: A contraindication for this therapy.

properties.label: indication
properties.comment: A factor that indicates use of this therapy for treatment and/or prevention of a condition, symptom, etc. For therapies such as drugs, indications can include both officially-approved indications as well as off-label uses. These can be distinguished by using the ApprovedIndication subtype of MedicalIndication.

properties.label: postOp
properties.comment: A description of the postoperative procedures, care, and/or followups for this device.

properties.label: preOp
properties.comment: A description of the workup, testing, and other preparations required before implanting this device.

properties.label: procedure
properties.comment: A description of the procedure involved in setting up, using, and/or installing the device.

properties.label: purpose
properties.comment: A goal towards an action is taken. Can be concrete or abstract.

properties.label: seriousAdverseOutcome
properties.comment: A possible serious complication and/or serious side effect of this therapy. Serious adverse outcomes include those that are life-threatening; result in death, disability, or permanent damage; require hospitalization or prolong existing hospitalization; cause congenital anomalies or birth defects; or jeopardize the patient and may require medical or surgical intervention to prevent one of the outcomes in this definition.

label: MedicalDevicePurpose
comment: Categories of medical devices, organized by the purpose or intended use of the device.

label: MedicalEvidenceLevel
comment: Level of evidence for a medical guideline. Enumerated type.

label: MedicalGuideline
comment: Any recommendation made by a standard society (e.g. ACC/AHA) or consensus statement that denotes how to diagnose and treat a particular condition. Note: this type should be used to tag the actual guideline recommendation; if the guideline recommendation occurs in a larger scholarly article, use MedicalScholarlyArticle to tag the overall article, not this type. Note also: the organization making the recommendation should be captured in the recognizingAuthority base property of MedicalEntity.

properties.label: evidenceLevel
properties.comment: Strength of evidence of the data used to formulate the guideline (enumerated).

properties.label: evidenceOrigin
properties.comment: Source of the data used to formulate the guidance, e.g. RCT, consensus opinion, etc.

properties.label: guidelineDate
properties.comment: Date on which this guideline's recommendation was made.

properties.label: guidelineSubject
properties.comment: The medical conditions, treatments, etc. that are the subject of the guideline.

label: MedicalGuidelineContraindication
comment: A guideline contraindication that designates a process as harmful and where quality of the data supporting the contraindication is sound.

label: MedicalGuidelineRecommendation
comment: A guideline recommendation that is regarded as efficacious and where quality of the data supporting the recommendation is sound.

properties.label: recommendationStrength
properties.comment: Strength of the guideline's recommendation (e.g. 'class I').

label: MedicalImagingTechnique
comment: Any medical imaging modality typically used for diagnostic purposes. Enumerated type.

label: MedicalStudy
comment: A medical study is an umbrella type covering all kinds of research studies relating to human medicine or health, including observational studies and interventional trials and registries, randomized, controlled or not. When the specific type of study is known, use one of the extensions of this type, such as MedicalTrial or MedicalObservationalStudy. Also, note that this type should be used to mark up data that describes the study itself; to tag an article that publishes the results of a study, use MedicalScholarlyArticle. Note: use the code property of MedicalEntity to store study IDs, e.g. clinicaltrials.gov ID.

properties.label: outcome
properties.comment: Expected or actual outcomes of the study.

properties.label: population
properties.comment: Any characteristics of the population used in the study, e.g. 'males under 65'.

properties.label: sponsor
properties.comment: Sponsor of the study.

properties.label: status
properties.comment: The status of the study (enumerated).

properties.label: studyLocation
properties.comment: The location in which the study is taking/took place.

properties.label: studySubject
properties.comment: A subject of the study, i.e. one of the medical conditions, therapies, devices, drugs, etc. investigated by the study.

label: MedicalObservationalStudy
comment: An observational study is a type of medical study that attempts to infer the possible effect of a treatment through observation of a cohort of subjects over a period of time. In an observational study, the assignment of subjects into treatment groups versus control groups is outside the control of the investigator. This is in contrast with controlled studies, such as the randomized controlled trials represented by MedicalTrial, where each subject is randomly assigned to a treatment group or a control group before the start of the treatment.

properties.label: studyDesign
properties.comment: Specifics about the observational study design (enumerated).

label: MedicalObservationalStudyDesign
comment: Design models for observational medical studies. Enumerated type.

label: MedicalProcedureType
comment: An enumeration that describes different types of medical procedures.

label: MedicalRiskEstimator
comment: Any rule set or interactive tool for estimating the risk of developing a complication or condition.

properties.label: estimatesRiskOf
properties.comment: The condition, complication, or symptom whose risk is being estimated.

properties.label: includedRiskFactor
properties.comment: A modifiable or non-modifiable risk factor included in the calculation, e.g. age, coexisting condition.

label: MedicalRiskCalculator
comment: A complex mathematical calculation requiring an online calculator, used to assess prognosis. Note: use the url property of Thing to record any URLs for online calculators.

label: MedicalRiskFactor
comment: A risk factor is anything that increases a person's likelihood of developing or contracting a disease, medical condition, or complication.

properties.label: increasesRiskOf
properties.comment: The condition, complication, etc. influenced by this factor.

label: MedicalRiskScore
comment: A simple system that adds up the number of risk factors to yield a score that is associated with prognosis, e.g. CHAD score, TIMI risk score.

properties.label: algorithm
properties.comment: The algorithm or rules to follow to compute the score.

label: ScholarlyArticle
comment: A scholarly article.

label: MedicalScholarlyArticle
comment: A scholarly article in the medical domain.

properties.label: publicationType
properties.comment: The type of the medical article, taken from the US NLM MeSH <a href=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/pubtypes.html>publication type catalog.

label: MedicalSignOrSymptom
comment: Any indication of the existence of a medical condition or disease.

properties.label: cause
properties.comment: An underlying cause. More specifically, one of the causative agent(s) that are most directly responsible for the pathophysiologic process that eventually results in the occurrence.

properties.label: possibleTreatment

properties.label: identifyingExam

properties.label: identifyingTest

label: MedicalSymptom

label: MedicalTestPanel

label: SuperficialAnatomy
comment: Anatomical features that can be observed by sight (without dissection), including the form and proportions of the human body as well as surface landmarks that correspond to deeper subcutaneous structures. Superficial anatomy plays an important role in sports medicine, phlebotomy, and other medical specialties as underlying anatomical structures can be identified through surface palpation. For example, during back surgery, superficial anatomy can be used to palpate and count vertebrae to find the site of incision. Or in phlebotomy, superficial anatomy can be used to locate an underlying vein; for example, the median cubital vein can be located by palpating the borders of the cubital fossa (such as the epicondyles of the humerus) and then looking for the superficial signs of the vein, such as size, prominence, ability to refill after depression, and feel of surrounding tissue support. As another example, in a subluxation (dislocation) of the glenohumeral joint, the bony structure becomes pronounced with the deltoid muscle failing to cover the glenohumeral joint allowing the edges of the scapula to be superficially visible. Here, the superficial anatomy is the visible edges of the scapula, implying the underlying dislocation of the joint (the related anatomical structure).

properties.comment: The currency (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format) of the price or a price component, when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

label: DeliveryChargeSpecification
comment: The price for the delivery of an offer using a particular delivery method.

properties.label: appliesToDeliveryMethod
properties.comment: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

properties.label: eligibleRegion
properties.comment: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.

label: DeliveryMethod
comment:
A delivery method is a standardized procedure for transferring the product or service to the destination of fulfillment chosen by the customer. Delivery methods are characterized by the means of transportation used, and by the organization or group that is the contracting party for the sending organization or person.

    Commonly used values:

    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeDirectDownload
    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeFreight
    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeMail
    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeOwnFleet
    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModePickUp
    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DHL
    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#FederalExpress
    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#UPS

label: Demand
comment: A demand entity represents the public, not necessarily binding, not necessarily exclusive, announcement by an organization or person to seek a certain type of goods or services. For describing demand using this type, the very same properties used for Offer apply.

properties.label: acceptedPaymentMethod
properties.comment: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.

properties.label: advanceBookingRequirement
properties.comment: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

properties.label: availability
properties.comment: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

properties.label: availabilityEnds
properties.comment: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

properties.label: availabilityStarts
properties.comment: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

properties.label: availableAtOrFrom
properties.comment: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

properties.label: availableDeliveryMethod
properties.comment: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

properties.label: businessFunction
properties.comment: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

properties.label: deliveryLeadTime
properties.comment: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods leaving the warehouse.

properties.label: eligibleCustomerType
properties.comment: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

properties.label: eligibleDuration
properties.comment: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

properties.label: eligibleQuantity
properties.comment: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

properties.label: eligibleRegion
properties.comment: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.

properties.label: eligibleTransactionVolume
properties.comment: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

properties.label: gtin13
properties.comment: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceeding zero.

properties.label: gtin14
properties.comment: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

properties.label: gtin8
properties.comment: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN.

properties.label: includesObject
properties.comment: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in the offer.

properties.label: inventoryLevel
properties.comment: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

properties.label: itemCondition
properties.comment: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition or a textual description of the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer.

properties.label: itemOffered
properties.comment: The item being offered.

properties.label: mpn
properties.comment: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

properties.label: priceSpecification
properties.comment: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

properties.label: seller
properties.comment: The organization or person making the offer.

properties.label: serialNumber
properties.comment: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

properties.label: sku
properties.comment: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

properties.label: validFrom
properties.comment: The date when the item becomes valid.

properties.label: validThrough
properties.comment: The end of the validity of offer, price specification, or opening hours data.

properties.label: warranty
properties.comment: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

label: IndividualProduct
comment: A single, identifiable product instance (e.g. a laptop with a particular serial number).

properties.label: serialNumber
properties.comment: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

label: OpeningHoursSpecification
comment: A structured value providing information about the opening hours of a place or a certain service inside a place.

properties.label: closes
properties.comment: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

properties.label: dayOfWeek
properties.comment: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

properties.label: opens
properties.comment: The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

properties.label: validFrom
properties.comment: The date when the item becomes valid.

properties.label: validThrough
properties.comment: The end of the validity of offer, price specification, or opening hours data.

label: OwnershipInfo
comment: A structured value providing information about when a certain organization or person owned a certain product.

properties.label: acquiredFrom
properties.comment: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

properties.label: ownedFrom
properties.comment: The date and time of obtaining the product.

properties.label: ownedThrough
properties.comment: The date and time of giving up ownership on the product.

properties.label: typeOfGood
properties.comment: The product that this structured value is referring to.

label: ParcelService
comment:
A private parcel service as the delivery mode available for a certain offer.

    Commonly used values:

    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DHL
    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#FederalExpress
    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#UPS

label: PaymentChargeSpecification
comment: The costs of settling the payment using a particular payment method.

properties.label: appliesToDeliveryMethod
properties.comment: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

properties.label: appliesToPaymentMethod
properties.comment: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

label: ProductModel
comment: A datasheet or vendor specification of a product (in the sense of a prototypical description).

properties.label: isVariantOf
properties.comment: A pointer to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive.

properties.label: predecessorOf
properties.comment: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

properties.label: successorOf
properties.comment: A pointer from a newer variant of a product  to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

label: QualitativeValue
comment: A predefined value for a product characteristic, e.g. the the power cord plug type "US" or the garment sizes "S", "M", "L", and "XL"

properties.label: equal
properties.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

properties.label: greater
properties.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

properties.label: greaterOrEqual
properties.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.

properties.label: lesser
properties.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

properties.label: lesserOrEqual
properties.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

properties.label: nonEqual
properties.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

properties.label: valueReference
properties.comment: A pointer to a secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature.

label: QuantitativeValue
comment: A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes.

properties.label: maxValue
properties.comment: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

properties.label: minValue
properties.comment: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

properties.label: unitCode
properties.comment: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters).

properties.label: value
properties.comment: The value of the product characteristic.

properties.label: valueReference
properties.comment: A pointer to a secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature.

label: SomeProducts
comment: A placeholder for multiple similar products of the same kind.

properties.label: inventoryLevel
properties.comment: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

label: TypeAndQuantityNode
comment: A structured value indicating the quantity, unit of measurement, and business function of goods included in a bundle offer.

properties.label: amountOfThisGood
properties.comment: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

properties.label: businessFunction
properties.comment: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

properties.label: typeOfGood
properties.comment: The product that this structured value is referring to.

properties.label: unitCode
properties.comment: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters).

label: UnitPriceSpecification
comment: The price asked for a given offer by the respective organization or person.

properties.label: billingIncrement
properties.comment: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

properties.label: priceType
properties.comment: A short text or acronym indicating multiple price specifications for the same offer, e.g. SRP for the suggested retail price or INVOICE for the invoice price, mostly used in the car industry.

properties.label: unitCode
properties.comment: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters).

label: WarrantyPromise
comment: A structured value representing the duration and scope of services that will be provided to a customer free of charge in case of a defect or malfunction of a product.

properties.label: durationOfWarranty
properties.comment: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

properties.label: warrantyScope
properties.comment: The scope of the warranty promise.

label: WarrantyScope
comment:
A range of of services that will be provided to a customer free of charge in case of a defect or malfunction of a product.

    Commonly used values:

    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Labor-BringIn
    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PartsAndLabor-BringIn
    http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PartsAndLabor-PickUp

label: TechArticle
comment: A technical article - Example: How-to (task) topics, step-by-step, procedural troubleshooting, specifications, etc.

properties.label: dependencies
properties.comment: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

properties.label: proficiencyLevel
properties.comment: Proficiency needed for this content; expected values: 'Beginner', 'Expert'.

label: APIReference
comment: Reference documentation for application programming interfaces (APIs).

properties.label: assembly
properties.comment: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll

properties.label: assemblyVersion
properties.comment: Associated product/technology version. e.g., .NET Framework 4.5

properties.label: programmingModel
properties.comment: Indicates whether API is managed or unmanaged.

properties.label: targetPlatform
properties.comment: Type of app development: phone, Metro style, desktop, XBox, etc.

label: Code
comment: Computer programming source code. Example: Full (compile ready) solutions, code snippet samples, scripts, templates.

properties.label: codeRepository
properties.comment: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, github, CodePlex)

properties.label: programmingLanguage
properties.comment: The computer programming language.

properties.label: runtime
properties.comment: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (Example - Java v1, Python2.3, .Net Framework 3.0)

properties.label: sampleType
properties.comment: Full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

properties.label: targetProduct
properties.comment: Target Operating System / Product to which the code applies.  If applies to several versions, just the product name can be used.

label: ParentAudience
comment: A set of characteristics describing parents, who can be interested in viewing some content

properties.label: childMaxAge
properties.comment: Maximal age of the child

properties.label: childMinAge
properties.comment: Minimal age of the child

label: AlignmentObject
comment: An intangible item that describes an alignment between a learning resource and a node in an educational framework.

properties.label: alignmentType
properties.comment: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'assesses', 'teaches', 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', 'educationalSubject', and 'educationLevel'.

properties.label: educationalFramework
properties.comment: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

properties.label: targetDescription
properties.comment: The description of a node in an established educational framework.

properties.label: targetName
properties.comment: The name of a node in an established educational framework.

properties.label: targetUrl
properties.comment: The URL of a node in an established educational framework.

label: EducationalAudience
comment: An EducationalAudience

properties.label: educationalRole
properties.comment: An educationalRole of an EducationalAudience

label: DataCatalog
comment: A collection of datasets.

properties.label: dataset
properties.comment: A dataset contained in a catalog.

label: DataDownload
comment: A dataset in downloadable form.

label: Dataset
comment: A body of structured information describing some topic(s) of interest.

properties.label: catalog
properties.comment: A data catalog which contains a dataset.

properties.label: distribution
properties.comment: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format.

properties.label: spatial
properties.comment: The range of spatial applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a dataset of New York weather, the state of New York.

properties.label: temporal
properties.comment: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

label: Class
comment: A class, also often called a 'Type'; equivalent to rdfs:Class.

label: Property
comment: A property, used to indicate attributes and relationships of some Thing; equivalent to rdf:Property.

properties.label: domainIncludes
properties.comment: Relates a property to a class that is (one of) the type(s) the property is expected to be used on.

properties.label: inverseOf
properties.comment: Relates a property to a property that is its inverse. Inverse properties relate the same pairs of items to each other, but in reversed direction. For example, the 'alumni' and 'alumniOf' properties are inverseOf each other. Some properties don't have explicit inverses; in these situations RDFa and JSON-LD syntax for reverse properties can be used.

properties.label: supercededBy
properties.comment: Relates a property to one that supercedes it.

properties.label: rangeIncludes
properties.comment: Relates a property to a class that constitutes (one of) the expected type(s) for values of the property.

label: PublicationEvent
comment: A PublicationEvent corresponds indifferently to the event of publication for a CreativeWork of any type e.g. a broadcast event, an on-demand event, a book/journal publication via a variety of delivery media.

properties.label: free
properties.comment: A flag to signal that the publication is accessible for free.

properties.label: publishedOn
properties.comment: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

label: BroadcastEvent
comment: An over the air or online broadcast event.

label: BroadcastService
comment: A delivery service through which content is provided via broadcast over the air or online.

properties.label: area
properties.comment: The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.

properties.label: broadcaster
properties.comment: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.

properties.label: parentService
properties.comment: A broadcast service to which the broadcast service may belong to such as regional variations of a national channel.

label: Clip
comment: A short TV or radio program or a segment/part of a program.

properties.label: clipNumber
properties.comment: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.

properties.label: partOfEpisode
properties.comment: The episode to which this clip belongs.

properties.label: partOfSeason
properties.comment: The season to which this episode belongs.

properties.label: partOfSeries
properties.comment: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

properties.label: position
properties.comment: Free text to define other than pure numerical ranking of an episode or a season in an ordered list of items (further formatting restrictions may apply within particular user groups).

properties.label: publication
properties.comment: A publication event associated with the episode, clip or media object.

label: OnDemandEvent
comment: A publication event e.g. catch-up TV or radio podcast, during which a program is available on-demand.

label: RadioClip
comment: A short radio program or a segment/part of a radio program.

properties.label: partOfSeason
properties.comment: The season to which this episode belongs.

properties.label: partOfSeries
properties.comment: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

label: RadioEpisode
comment: A radio episode which can be part of a series or season.

properties.comment: A cast member of the movie, tv/radio series, season, episode, or video.

properties.label: director
properties.comment: The director of the movie, tv/radio episode or series.

properties.label: musicBy
properties.comment: The composer of the movie or TV/radio soundtrack.

properties.label: partOfSeason
properties.comment: The season to which this episode belongs.

properties.label: partOfSeries
properties.comment: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

properties.label: producer
properties.comment: The producer of the movie, tv/radio series, season, or episode, or video.

properties.label: productionCompany
properties.comment: The production company or studio that made the movie, tv/radio series, season, or episode, or media object.

properties.label: trailer
properties.comment: The trailer of a movie or tv/radio series, season, or episode.

label: RadioSeason
comment: Season dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

properties.label: episode
properties.comment: An episode of a TV/radio series or season

properties.label: numberOfEpisodes
properties.comment: The number of episodes in this season or series.

properties.label: partOfSeries
properties.comment: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

properties.label: trailer
properties.comment: The trailer of a movie or tv/radio series, season, or episode.

label: RadioSeries
comment: Series dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

properties.label: actor
properties.comment: A cast member of the movie, tv/radio series, season, episode, or video.

properties.label: director
properties.comment: The director of the movie, tv/radio episode or series.

properties.label: episode
properties.comment: An episode of a TV/radio series or season

properties.comment: The composer of the movie or TV/radio soundtrack.

properties.comment: The number of episodes in this season or series.

properties.label: producer

properties.label: productionCompany
properties.comment: The production company or studio that made the movie, tv/radio series, season, or episode, or media object.

properties.label: season
properties.comment: A season in a tv/radio series.

properties.label: trailer
properties.comment: The trailer of a movie or tv/radio series, season, or episode.

label: TVClip
comment: A short TV program or a segment/part of a TV program.

properties.label: partOfSeason
properties.comment: The season to which this episode belongs.

properties.label: partOfSeries
properties.comment: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

label: BusinessAudience
comment: A set of characteristics belonging to businesses, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.

properties.label: numberofEmployees
properties.comment: The size of business by number of employees.

properties.label: yearlyRevenue
properties.comment: The size of the business in annual revenue.

properties.label: yearsInOperation
properties.comment: The age of the business.

label: ContactPointOption
comment: Enumerated options related to a ContactPoint

label: Permit
comment: A permit issued by an organization, e.g. a parking pass.

properties.label: issuedThrough
properties.comment: The service through with the permit was granted.

properties.label: permitAudience
properties.comment: The target audience for this permit.

properties.label: validFor
properties.comment: The time validity of the permit.

properties.label: validFrom
properties.comment: The date when the item becomes valid.

properties.label: validIn
properties.comment: The geographic area where the permit is valid.

properties.label: validUntil
properties.comment: The date when the item is no longer valid.

properties.label: issuedBy
properties.comment: The organization issuing the ticket or permit.

label: GovernmentPermit
comment: A permit issued by a government agency.

label: Service
comment: A service provided by an organization, e.g. delivery service, print services, etc.

properties.label: availableChannel
properties.comment: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.)

properties.label: produces
properties.comment: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

properties.label: serviceArea
properties.comment: The geographic area where the service is provided.

properties.label: serviceAudience
properties.comment: The audience eligible for this service.

properties.label: serviceType
properties.comment: The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

properties.label: provider
properties.comment: The person or organization providing the service, reservation, or creative work. The provider may subcontract out the service.

label: GovernmentService
comment: A service provided by a government organization, e.g. food stamps, veterans benefits, etc.

properties.label: serviceOperator
properties.comment: The operating organization, if different from the provider.  This enables the representation of services that are provided by an organization, but operated by another organization like a subcontractor.

label: ServiceChannel
comment: A means for accessing a service, e.g. a government office location, web site, or phone number.

properties.label: availableLanguage
properties.comment: A language someone may use with the item.

properties.label: processingTime
properties.comment: Estimated processing time for the service using this channel.

properties.label: providesService
properties.comment: The service provided by this channel.

properties.label: serviceLocation
properties.comment: The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

properties.label: servicePhone
properties.comment: The phone number to use to access the service.

properties.label: servicePostalAddress
properties.comment: The address for accessing the service by mail.

properties.label: serviceSmsNumber
properties.comment: The number to access the service by text message.

properties.label: serviceUrl
properties.comment: The website to access the service.

label: EventStatusType
comment: EventStatusType is an enumeration type whose instances represent several states that an Event may be in.

label: DeliveryEvent
comment: An event involving the delivery of an item.

properties.label: accessCode
properties.comment: Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).

properties.label: availableFrom
properties.comment: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.

properties.label: availableThrough
properties.comment: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.

properties.label: hasDeliveryMethod
properties.comment: Method used for delivery or shipping.

label: LockerDelivery
comment: A DeliveryMethod in which an item is made available via locker.
