comment: An order is a confirmation of a transaction (a receipt), which can contain multiple line items, each represented by an Offer that has been accepted by the customer.

properties.label: acceptedOffer
properties.comment: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.

properties.label: billingAddress
properties.comment: The billing address for the order.

properties.label: confirmationNumber
properties.comment: A number that confirms the given order.

properties.label: customer
properties.comment: Party placing the order.

properties.label: discount
properties.comment: Any discount applied (to an Order).

properties.label: discountCode
properties.comment: Code used to redeem a discount.

properties.label: discountCurrency
properties.comment: The currency (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format) of the discount.

properties.label: isGift
properties.comment: Was the offer accepted as a gift for someone other than the buyer.

properties.label: merchant
properties.comment: The party taking the order (e.g. Amazon.com is a merchant for many sellers).

properties.label: orderDate
properties.comment: Date order was placed.

properties.label: orderedItem
properties.comment: The item ordered.

properties.label: orderNumber
properties.comment: The identifier of the transaction.

properties.label: orderStatus
properties.comment: The current status of the order.

properties.label: paymentDue
properties.comment: The date that payment is due.

properties.label: paymentMethod
properties.comment: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

properties.label: paymentMethodId
properties.comment: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

properties.label: paymentUrl
properties.comment: The URL for sending a payment.

label: OrderStatus
comment: Enumerated status values for Order.

label: ParcelDelivery
comment: The delivery of a parcel either via the postal service or a commercial service.

properties.label: carrier
properties.comment: The party responsible for the parcel delivery.

properties.label: deliveryAddress
properties.comment: Destination address.

properties.label: deliveryStatus
properties.comment: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

properties.label: expectedArrivalFrom
properties.comment: The earliest date the package may arrive.

properties.label: expectedArrivalUntil
properties.comment: The latest date the package may arrive.

properties.label: hasDeliveryMethod
properties.comment: Method used for delivery or shipping.

properties.label: itemShipped
properties.comment: Item(s) being shipped.

properties.label: originAddress
properties.comment: Shipper's address.

properties.label: partOfOrder
properties.comment: The overall order the items in this delivery were included in.

properties.label: trackingNumber
properties.comment: Shipper tracking number.

properties.label: trackingUrl
properties.comment: Tracking url for the parcel delivery.

label: Action
comment: An action performed by a direct agent and indirect     participants upon a direct object. Optionally happens at a location     with the help of an inanimate instrument. The execution of the action     may produce a result. Specific action sub-type documentation specifies     the exact expectation of each argument/role.

properties.label: agent
properties.comment: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). e.g. *John* wrote a book.

properties.label: endTime
properties.comment:
The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

properties.label: instrument
properties.comment: The object that helped the agent perform the action. e.g. John wrote a book with *a pen*.

properties.label: location
properties.comment: The location of the event, organization or action.

properties.label: object
properties.comment: The object upon the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). e.g. John read *a book*.

properties.label: participant
properties.comment: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. e.g. John wrote a book with *Steve*.

properties.label: result
properties.comment: The result produced in the action. e.g. John wrote *a book*.

properties.label: startTime
properties.comment:
The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

properties.label: actionStatus
properties.comment: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

properties.label: target
properties.comment: Indicates a target EntryPoint for an Action.

label: OrganizeAction
comment: The act of manipulating/administering/supervising/controlling one or more objects.

label: AllocateAction
comment: The act of organizing tasks/objects/events by associating resources to it.

properties.label: purpose
properties.comment: A goal towards an action is taken. Can be concrete or abstract.

label: AcceptAction
comment:
The act of committing to/adopting an object.

Related actions:

  • RejectAction: The antagonym of AcceptAction.

label: AchieveAction
comment: The act of accomplishing something via     previous efforts. It is an instantaneous action rather than an ongoing     process.

label: UpdateAction
comment: The act of managing by changing/editing the state of the object.

properties.label: collection
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

label: AddAction
comment: The act of editing by adding an object to a collection.

label: AssessAction
comment: The act of forming one's opinion, reaction or sentiment.

label: ReactAction
comment: The act of responding instinctively and emotionally to an object, expressing a sentiment.

label: AgreeAction
comment: The act of expressing a consistency of opinion with the object. An agent agrees to/about an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

label: InsertAction
comment: The act of adding at a specific location in an ordered collection.

properties.label: toLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

label: AppendAction
comment: The act of inserting at the end if an ordered collection.

label: ApplyAction
comment:
The act of registering to an organization/service without the guarantee to receive it. NOTE(goto): should this be under InteractAction instead?

Related actions:

  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, ApplyAction has no guarantees that the application will be accepted.

label: MoveAction
comment:
The act of an agent relocating to a place.

Related actions:

  • TransferAction: Unlike TransferAction, the subject of the move is a living Person or Organization rather than an inanimate object.

properties.label: fromLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

properties.label: toLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

label: ArriveAction
comment: The act of arriving at a place. An agent arrives at a destination from an fromLocation, optionally with participants.

label: InteractAction
comment: The act of interacting with another person or organization.

label: CommunicateAction
comment: The act of conveying information to another person via a communication medium (instrument) such as speech, email, or telephone conversation.

properties.label: about
properties.comment: The subject matter of the content.

properties.label: language
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

label: AskAction
comment:
The act of posing a question / favor to someone.

Related actions:

  • ReplyAction: Appears generally as a response to AskAction.

properties.label: question
properties.comment: A sub property of object. A question.

label: AssignAction
comment: The act of allocating an action/event/task to some destination (someone or something).

label: AuthorizeAction
comment: The act of granting permission to an object.

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

label: BefriendAction
comment:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone (object) mutually/bidirectionally/symmetrically.

Related actions:

  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, BefriendAction implies that the connection is reciprocal.

label: BookmarkAction
comment: An agent bookmarks/flags/labels/tags/marks an object.

label: TransferAction
comment: The act of transferring/moving (abstract or concrete) animate or inanimate objects from one place to another.

properties.label: fromLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

properties.label: toLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

label: BorrowAction
comment:
The act of obtaining an object under an agreement to return it at a later date. Reciprocal of LendAction.

Related actions:

  • LendAction: Reciprocal of BorrowAction.

properties.label: lender
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

label: TradeAction
comment: The act of participating in an exchange of goods and services for monetary compensation. An agent trades an object, product or service with a participant in exchange for a one time or periodic payment.

properties.label: price
properties.comment: The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

label: BuyAction
comment: The act of giving money to a seller in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent buys an object, product, or service from a seller for a price. Reciprocal of SellAction.

properties.label: vendor
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The seller. The participant/person/organization that sold the object.

properties.label: warrantyPromise
properties.comment: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

label: PlanAction
comment: The act of planning the execution of an event/task/action/reservation/plan to a future date.

properties.label: scheduledTime
properties.comment: The time the object is scheduled to.

label: CancelAction
comment:
The act of asserting that a future event/action is no longer going to happen.

Related actions:

  • ConfirmAction: The antagonym of CancelAction.

label: FindAction
comment:
The act of finding an object.

Related actions:

  • SearchAction: FindAction is generally lead by a SearchAction, but not necessarily.

label: CheckAction
comment: An agent inspects/determines/investigates/inquire or examine an object's accuracy/quality/condition or state.

label: CheckInAction
comment:
The act of an agent communicating (service provider, social media, etc) their arrival by registering/confirming for a previously reserved service (e.g. flight check in) or at a place (e.g. hotel), possibly resulting in a result (boarding pass, etc).

Related actions:

  • CheckOutAction: The antagonym of CheckInAction.
  • ArriveAction: Unlike ArriveAction, CheckInAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the start of a previously reserved service.
  • ConfirmAction: Unlike ConfirmAction, CheckInAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the *start* of a previously reserved service rather than its validity/existence.

label: CheckOutAction
comment:
The act of an agent communicating (service provider, social media, etc) their departure of a previously reserved service (e.g. flight check in) or place (e.g. hotel).

Related actions:

  • CheckInAction: The antagonym of CheckOutAction.
  • DepartAction: Unlike DepartAction, CheckOutAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the end of a previously reserved service.
  • CancelAction: Unlike CancelAction, CheckOutAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the end of a previously reserved service.

label: ChooseAction
comment: The act of expressing a preference from a set of options or a large or unbounded set of choices/options.

properties.label: option
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

label: CommentAction
comment: The act of generating a comment about a subject.

label: InformAction
comment: The act of notifying someone of information pertinent to them, with no expectation of a response.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place or organization.

label: ConfirmAction
comment:
The act of notifying someone that a future event/action is going to happen as expected.

Related actions:

  • CancelAction: The antagonym of ConfirmAction.

label: ConsumeAction
comment: The act of ingesting information/resources/food.

label: CreateAction
comment: The act of deliberately creating/producing/generating/building a result out of the agent.

label: CookAction
comment: The act of producing/preparing food.

properties.label: foodEstablishment
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.

properties.label: foodEvent
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

properties.label: recipe
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.

label: DeleteAction
comment: The act of editing a recipient by removing one of its objects.

label: DepartAction
comment: The act of  departing from a place. An agent departs from an fromLocation for a destination, optionally with participants.

label: DisagreeAction
comment: The act of expressing a difference of opinion with the object. An agent disagrees to/about an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

label: DiscoverAction
comment: The act of discovering/finding an object.

label: DislikeAction
comment: The act of expressing a negative sentiment about the object. An agent dislikes an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

label: DonateAction
comment: The act of providing goods, services, or money without compensation, often for philanthropic reasons.

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

label: DownloadAction
comment: The act of downloading an object.

label: DrawAction
comment: The act of producing a visual/graphical representation of an object, typically with a pen/pencil and paper as instruments.

label: DrinkAction
comment: The act of swallowing liquids.

label: EatAction
comment: The act of swallowing solid objects.

label: EndorseAction
comment: An agent approves/certifies/likes/supports/sanction an object.

properties.label: endorsee
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

label: PlayAction
comment:
The act of playing/exercising/training/performing for enjoyment, leisure, recreation, Competition or exercise.

Related actions:

  • ListenAction: Unlike ListenAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to performing for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming music.
  • WatchAction: Unlike WatchAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to showing/displaying for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming visual content.

properties.label: audience
properties.comment: The intended audience of the item, i.e. the group for whom the item was created.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place or organization.

label: ExerciseAction
comment: The act of participating in exertive activity for the purposes of improving health and fitness

properties.label: course
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

properties.label: diet
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

properties.label: distance
properties.comment: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

properties.label: exercisePlan
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The exercise plan used on this action.

properties.label: exerciseType
properties.comment: Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.

properties.label: fromLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

properties.label: opponent
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.

properties.label: sportsActivityLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.

properties.label: sportsEvent
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

properties.label: sportsTeam
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

properties.label: toLocation
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

label: FilmAction
comment: The act of capturing sound and moving images on film, video, or digitally.

label: FollowAction
comment:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone/something (object) unidirectionally/asymmetrically to get updates polled from.

Related actions:

  • BefriendAction: Unlike BefriendAction, FollowAction implies that the connection is *not* necessarily reciprocal.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, FollowAction implies that the follower acts as an active agent constantly/actively polling for updates.
  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, FollowAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.
  • JoinAction: Unlike JoinAction, FollowAction implies that the agent is interested in getting updates from the object.
  • TrackAction: Unlike TrackAction, FollowAction refers to the polling of updates of all aspects of animate objects rather than the location of inanimate objects (e.g. you track a package, but you don't follow it).

properties.label: followee
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.

label: GiveAction
comment:
The act of transferring ownership of an object to a destination. Reciprocal of TakeAction.

Related actions:

  • TakeAction: Reciprocal of GiveAction.
  • SendAction: Unlike SendAction, GiveAction implies that ownership is being transferred (e.g. I may send my laptop to you, but that doesn't mean I'm giving it to you).

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

label: IgnoreAction
comment: The act of intentionally disregarding the object. An agent ignores an object.

label: InstallAction
comment: The act of installing an application.

label: InviteAction
comment: The act of asking someone to attend an event. Reciprocal of RsvpAction.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place or organization.

label: JoinAction
comment:
An agent joins an event/group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, JoinAction refers to joining a group/team of people.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be receiving updates.
  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be polling for updates.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place or organization.

label: LeaveAction
comment:
An agent leaves an event / group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

  • JoinAction: The antagonym of LeaveAction.
  • UnRegisterAction: Unlike UnRegisterAction, LeaveAction implies leaving a group/team of people rather than a service.

properties.label: event
properties.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place or organization.

label: LendAction
comment:
The act of providing an object under an agreement that it will be returned at a later date. Reciprocal of BorrowAction.

Related actions:

  • BorrowAction: Reciprocal of LendAction.

properties.label: borrower
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.

label: LikeAction
comment: The act of expressing a positive sentiment about the object. An agent likes an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

label: ListenAction
comment: The act of consuming audio content.

label: LoseAction
comment: The act of being defeated in a competitive activity.

properties.label: winner
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

label: MarryAction
comment: The act of marrying a person.

label: OrderAction
comment: An agent orders an object/product/service to be delivered/sent.

label: PaintAction
comment: The act of producing a painting, typically with paint and canvas as instruments.

label: PayAction
comment: An agent pays a price to a participant.

properties.label: purpose
properties.comment: A goal towards an action is taken. Can be concrete or abstract.

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

label: PerformAction
comment: The act of participating in performance arts.

properties.label: entertainmentBusiness
properties.comment: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.

label: PhotographAction
comment: The act of capturing still images of objects using a camera.

label: PrependAction
comment: The act of inserting at the beginning if an ordered collection.

label: QuoteAction
comment: An agent quotes/estimates/appraises an object/product/service with a price at a location/store.

label: ReadAction
comment: The act of consuming written content.

label: ReceiveAction
comment:
The act of physically/electronically taking delivery of an object thathas been transferred from an origin to a destination. Reciprocal of SendAction.

Related actions:

  • SendAction: The reciprocal of ReceiveAction.
  • TakeAction: Unlike TakeAction, ReceiveAction does not imply that the ownership has been transfered (e.g. I can receive a package, but it does not mean the package is now mine).

properties.label: deliveryMethod
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery

properties.label: sender
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

label: RegisterAction
comment:
The act of registering to be a user of a service, product or web page.

Related actions:

  • JoinAction: Unlike JoinAction, RegisterAction implies you are registering to be a user of a service, *not* a group/team of people.
  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting to poll for updates from the object.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting updates from the object.

label: RejectAction
comment:
The act of rejecting to/adopting an object.

Related actions:

  • AcceptAction: The antagonym of RejectAction.

label: RentAction
comment: The act of giving money in return for temporary use, but not ownership, of an object such as a vehicle or property. For example, an agent rents a property from a landlord in exchange for a periodic payment.

properties.label: landlord
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.

properties.label: realEstateAgent
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The real estate agent involved in the action.

label: ReplaceAction
comment: The act of editing a recipient by replacing an old object with a new object.

properties.label: replacee
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The object that is being replaced.

properties.label: replacer
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.

label: ReplyAction
comment:
The act of responding to a question/message asked/sent by the object. Related to AskAction.

Related actions:

  • AskAction: Appears generally as an origin of a ReplyAction.

label: ReserveAction
comment:
Reserving a concrete object.

Related actions:

  • ScheduleAction: Unlike ScheduleAction, ReserveAction reserves concrete objects (e.g. a table, a hotel) towards a time slot / spatial allocation.

properties.label: scheduledTime
properties.comment: The time the object is scheduled to.

label: ReturnAction
comment: The act of returning to the origin that which was previously received (concrete objects) or taken (ownership).

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

label: ReviewAction
comment: The act of producing a balanced opinion about the object for an audience. An agent reviews an object with participants resulting in a review.

properties.label: resultReview
properties.comment: A sub property of result. The review that resulted in the performing of the action.

label: RsvpAction
comment: The act of notifying an event organizer as to whether you expect to attend the event.

label: ScheduleAction
comment:
Scheduling future actions, events, or tasks.

Related actions:

  • ReserveAction: Unlike ReserveAction, ScheduleAction allocates future actions (e.g. an event, a task, etc) towards a time slot / spatial allocation.

label: SearchAction
comment:
The act of searching for an object.

Related actions:

  • FindAction: SearchAction generally leads to a FindAction, but not necessarily.

properties.label: query
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The query used on this action.

label: SellAction
comment: The act of taking money from a buyer in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent sells an object, product, or service to a buyer for a price. Reciprocal of BuyAction.

properties.label: buyer
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant/person/organization that bought the object.

properties.label: warrantyPromise
properties.comment: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

label: SendAction
comment:
The act of physically/electronically dispatching an object for transfer from an origin to a destination.

Related actions:

  • ReceiveAction: The reciprocal of SendAction.
  • GiveAction: Unlike GiveAction, SendAction does not imply the transfer of ownership (e.g. I can send you my laptop, but I'm not necessarily giving it to you).

properties.label: deliveryMethod
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

label: ShareAction
comment: The act of distributing content to people for their amusement or edification.

label: SubscribeAction
comment:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone/something (object) unidirectionally/asymmetrically to get updates pushed to.

Related actions:

  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, SubscribeAction implies that the subscriber acts as a passive agent being constantly/actively pushed for updates.
  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, SubscribeAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.
  • JoinAction: Unlike JoinAction, SubscribeAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.

label: TakeAction
comment:
The act of gaining ownership of an object from an origin. Reciprocal of GiveAction.

Related actions:

  • GiveAction: The reciprocal of TakeAction.
  • ReceiveAction: Unlike ReceiveAction, TakeAction implies that ownership has been transfered.

label: TieAction
comment: The act of reaching a draw in a competitive activity.

label: TipAction
comment: The act of giving money voluntarily to a beneficiary in recognition of services rendered.

properties.label: recipient
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

label: TrackAction
comment:
An agent tracks an object for updates.

Related actions:

  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, TrackAction refers to the interest on the location of innanimates objects.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, TrackAction refers to the interest on the location of innanimate objects.

properties.label: deliveryMethod
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery

label: TravelAction
comment: The act of traveling from an fromLocation to a destination by a specified mode of transport, optionally with participants.

properties.label: distance
properties.comment: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

label: UnRegisterAction
comment:
The act of un-registering from a service.

Related actions:

  • RegisterAction: Antagonym of UnRegisterAction.
  • Leave: Unlike LeaveAction, UnRegisterAction implies that you are unregistering from a service you werer previously registered, rather than leaving a team/group of people.

label: UseAction
comment: The act of applying an object to its intended purpose.

label: ViewAction
comment: The act of consuming static visual content.

label: VoteAction
comment: The act of expressing a preference from a fixed/finite/structured set of choices/options.

properties.label: candidate
properties.comment: A sub property of object. The candidate subject of this action.

label: WantAction
comment: The act of expressing a desire about the object. An agent wants an object.

label: WatchAction
comment: The act of consuming dynamic/moving visual content.

label: WearAction
comment: The act of dressing oneself in clothing.

label: WinAction
comment: The act of achieving victory in a competitive activity.

properties.label: loser
properties.comment: A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

label: WriteAction
comment: The act of authoring written creative content.

properties.label: language
properties.comment: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

label: Reservation
comment: Describes a reservation for travel, dining or an event. Some reservations require tickets.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, restaurant reservations, flights, or rental cars, use http://schema.org/Offer.

properties.label: reservationId
properties.comment: A unique identifier for the reservation.

properties.label: reservationStatus
properties.comment: The current status of the reservation.

properties.label: reservationFor
properties.comment: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant,etc. being reserved.

properties.label: underName
properties.comment: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

properties.label: provider
properties.comment: The person or organization providing the service, reservation, or creative work. The provider may subcontract out the service.

properties.label: bookingAgent
properties.comment: If the reservation was not booked directly through the provider, the third-party booking agent can be recorded through this property.

properties.label: bookingTime
properties.comment: The date and time the reservation was booked.

properties.label: modifiedTime
properties.comment: The date and time the reservation was modified.

properties.label: programMembershipUsed
properties.comment: Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

properties.label: reservedTicket
properties.comment: A ticket associated with the reservation.

properties.label: totalPrice
properties.comment: The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

properties.label: priceCurrency
properties.comment: The currency (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format) of the price or a price component, when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

label: BusReservation
comment: A reservation for bus travel.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use http://schema.org/Offer.

label: EventReservation
comment: A reservation for an event like a concert, sporting event, or lecture.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use http://schema.org/Offer.

label: FlightReservation
comment: A reservation for air travel.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use http://schema.org/Offer.

properties.label: boardingGroup
properties.comment: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

label: FoodEstablishmentReservation
comment: A reservation to dine at a food-related business.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

properties.label: endTime
properties.comment:
The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

properties.label: startTime
properties.comment:
The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

properties.label: partySize
properties.comment: Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

label: LodgingReservation
comment: A reservation for lodging at a hotel, motel, inn, etc.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

properties.label: checkinTime
properties.comment: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

properties.label: checkoutTime
properties.comment: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

properties.label: lodgingUnitType
properties.comment: Textual description of the unit type (including suite vs. room, size of bed, etc.).

properties.label: lodgingUnitDescription
properties.comment: A full description of the lodging unit.

properties.label: numAdults
properties.comment: The number of adults staying in the unit.

properties.label: numChildren
properties.comment: The number of children staying in the unit.

label: RentalCarReservation
comment: A reservation for a rental car.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

properties.label: pickupLocation
properties.comment: Where a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

properties.label: dropoffLocation
properties.comment: Where a rental car can be dropped off.

properties.label: pickupTime
properties.comment: When a taxi will pickup a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

properties.label: dropoffTime
properties.comment: When a rental car can be dropped off.

label: TaxiReservation
comment: A reservation for a taxi.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use http://schema.org/Offer.

label: TrainReservation
comment: A reservation for train travel.Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use http://schema.org/Offer.

label: ReservationPackage
comment: A group of multiple reservations with common values for all sub-reservations.

properties.label: subReservation
properties.comment: The individual reservations included in the package. Typically a repeated property.

label: ReservationStatusType
comment: Enumerated status values for Reservation.

label: Bus Trip
comment: A trip on a commercial bus line.

label: Train Trip
comment: A trip on a commercial train line.

label: Flight
comment: An airline flight.

properties.label: carrier
properties.comment: The party responsible for the parcel delivery.

properties.label: provider
properties.comment: The person or organization providing the service, reservation, or creative work. The provider may subcontract out the service.

properties.label: flightNumber
properties.comment: The unique identifier for a flight, not including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, the flightNumber is '110'. The IATA code can be set on the Airline.

properties.label: departureTime
properties.comment: The expected departure time.

properties.label: arrivalTime
properties.comment: The expected arrival time.

properties.label: departureAirport
properties.comment: The airport where the flight originates.

properties.label: departureAirport
properties.comment: The airport where the flight terminates.

properties.label: departureGate
properties.comment: Identifier of the flight's departure gate.

properties.label: arrivalGate
properties.comment: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.

properties.label: departureTerminal
properties.comment: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

properties.label: arrivalTerminal
properties.comment: Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.

properties.label: aircraft
properties.comment: The kind of aircraft (e.g., "Boeing 747").

properties.label: mealService
properties.comment: Description of the meals that will be provided or available for purchase.

properties.label: estimatedFlightDuration
properties.comment: The estimated time the flight will take.

properties.label: flightDistance
properties.comment: The distance of the flight.

properties.label: webCheckinTime
properties.comment: The time when a passenger can check into the flight online.

label: Airline
comment: An organization that provides flights for passengers.

properties.label: iataCode
properties.comment: IATA identifier for an airline or airport

label: Program Membership
comment: Used to describe membership in a loyalty programs (e.g. "StarAliance"), traveler clubs (e.g. "AAA"), purchase clubs ("Safeway Club"), etc.

label: Ticket
comment: Used to describe a ticket to an event, a flight, a bus ride, etc.

properties.label: underName
properties.comment: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

properties.label: totalPrice
properties.comment: The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

properties.label: priceCurrency
properties.comment: The currency (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format) of the price or a price component, when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

properties.label: issuedBy
properties.comment: The organization issuing the ticket or permit.

properties.label: dateIssued
properties.comment: The date the ticket was issued.

properties.label: ticketedSeat
properties.comment: The seat associated with the ticket.

properties.label: ticketNumber
properties.comment: The unique identifier for the ticket.

properties.label: ticketToken
properties.comment: Reference to an asset (e.g., Barcode, QR code image or PDF) usable for entrance.

label: Seat
comment: Used to describe a seat, such as a reserved seat in an event reservation.

properties.label: seatNumber
properties.comment: The location of the reserved seat (e.g., 27).

properties.label: seatRow
properties.comment: The row location of the reserved seat (e.g., B).

properties.label: seatSection
properties.comment: The section location of the reserved seat (e.g. Orchestra).

properties.label: seatingType
properties.comment: The type/class of the seat.

label: Taxi
comment: A taxi.

label: Vehicle
comment: A vehicle.

label: Car
comment: An automobile.

label: QAPage
comment: A QAPage is a WebPage focussed on a specific Question and its Answer(s), e.g. in a question answering site or documenting Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs).

label: Question
comment: A specific question - e.g. from a user seeking answers online, or collected in a Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) document.

properties.label: upvoteCount
properties.comment: The number of upvotes this question has received from the community.

properties.label: downvoteCount
properties.comment: The number of downvotes this question has received from the community.

properties.label: answerCount
properties.comment: The number of answers this question has received.

properties.label: acceptedAnswer
properties.comment: The answer that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.

properties.label: suggestedAnswer
properties.comment: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

label: Answer
comment: An answer offered to a question; perhaps correct, perhaps opinionated or wrong.

properties.label: upvoteCount
properties.comment: The number of upvotes this question has received from the community.

properties.label: downvoteCount
properties.comment: The number of downvotes this question has received from the community.

properties.label: parentItem
properties.comment: The parent of a question, answer or item in general.

label: EmailMessage
comment: An email message.

label: ActionStatusType
comment: The status of an Action.

label: EntryPoint
comment: An entry point, within some Web-based protocol.

properties.label: httpMethod
properties.comment: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.

properties.label: encodingType
properties.comment: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

properties.label: contentType
properties.comment: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

properties.label: application
properties.comment: An application that can complete the request.

properties.label: urlTemplate
properties.comment: An url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

label: PropertyValueSpecification
comment: A Property value specification.

properties.label: maxValue
properties.comment: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

properties.label: minValue
properties.comment: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

properties.label: valueName
properties.comment: Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

properties.label: valueRequired
properties.comment: Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action.  Default is false.

properties.label: defaultValue
properties.comment: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

properties.label: readonlyValue
properties.comment: Whether or not a property is mutable.  Default is false. Specifying this for a property that also has a value makes it act similar to a "hidden" input in an HTML form.

properties.label: multipleValues
properties.comment: Whether multiple values are allowed for the property.  Default is false.

properties.label: valueMinLength
properties.comment: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

properties.label: valueMaxLength
properties.comment: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

properties.label: valuePattern
properties.comment: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

properties.label: stepValue
properties.comment: The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

label: Role
comment: Represents additional information about a relationship or property. For example a Role can be used to say that a 'member' role linking some SportsTeam to a player occurred during a particular time period. Or that a Person's 'actor' role in a Movie was for some particular characterName. Such properties can be attached to a Role entity, which is then associated with the main entities using ordinary properties like 'member' or 'actor'.

properties.label: endDate
properties.comment: The end date and time of the role, event or item (in ISO 8601 date format).

properties.label: startDate
properties.comment: The start date and time of the event, role or item (in ISO 8601 date format).

label: PerformanceRole
comment: A PerformanceRole is a Role that some entity places with regard to a theatrical performance, e.g. in a Movie, TVSeries etc.

properties.label: characterName
properties.comment: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.

label: OrganizationRole
comment: A subclass of Role used to describe roles within organizations.

properties.label: namedPosition
properties.comment: A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.
